title: Facebook says it has registered 2.5 million people to vote
text: Facebook Inc. FB, -2.64% on Monday said it has helped register 2.5 million people to vote so far this year across its social-media platforms, already topping the 2 million registrations it logged in 2016 and 2018.

title: Facebook’s new Rights Manager tool lets creators protect their photos, including those embedded elsewhere
text: Facebook today is introducing a new tool that will allow rights holders to protect and manage their photos across both Facebook and Instagram. With the newly launched “Rights Manager for Images,” Facebook is offering creators and publishers access to content matching technology similar to what it introduced in 2016 to combat stolen videos.

title: 3 Reasons Facebook's Oculus Quest 2 Will Expand Its VR Market
text: The tech giant is trying to corner the market for stand-alone virtual reality headsets with its latest release.
